An estimated 75 per cent of our population relies on agriculture, yet only 10 per cent is arable land, according to the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations.Private freehold is held by individuals, groups of individuals, and private corporate persons. Land is an emotive topic in Kenya. It’s the most important factor of production given that agriculture is the engine of economic growth. An estimated 75 per cent of our population relies on agriculture, yet only 10 per cent is arable land, according to the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations.



