Twin challenge
Public and trust lands within the national and county governments’ jurisdiction are quite extensive. The government is the entity with direct control over how land is used in Kenya. In the west, countries have relied on public land to spur economic development.
The United States is an excellent example of a country that has leveraged public land to create jobs. Locally, we are faced with the twin challenge of a consistently growing population and an economy that is not creating enough jobs to keep up with the thousands of graduates, who flock the job market.



